cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with learning accurate 3D shape and camera pose from images, which is a problem commonly addressed in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a convolutional network to predict both shape and pose suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The use of point clouds and differentiable projection suggests a focus on graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of an ensemble of pose predictors and distillation suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
